omatography"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DCE02C0DE7E34A129431955003B6069B","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Fractions containing RNA polymerase were concentrated with Vivaspin\u00ae 500 \u00b5L 5K ultrafiltration spin columns washed with loading buffer several times and subjected to further purification on an ion-exchange MonoQ 5\/50 GL column, using fast protein liquid chromatography.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"081B9D0B43524FB497AA9D5233CB9D49","order_id":2,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The washing step is crucial for further purification! One has to be sure that the elution buffer is fully exchanged with washing buffer to ensure the binding of the RNA polymerase onto the Ion-exchange column.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871723,"guid":"955BBE57652E4070BCB038EBE5FF74AF","previous_id":871722,"previous_guid":"1FD1EF828A73421B95436DC4C0FACD47","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"7E776186821343C687B9F26CD862D3CA","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Ion-exchange Chromatography"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"2A809C89D6704527B511318665F93379","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The column was equilibrated with five column volumes (CV) of the loading buffer. The suspension was loaded onto the column with loading buffer and continuously washed until the OD280nm reading drops to the baseline. Then a gradient of 50 CV from 250mM to 600mM NaCl [10mM Tris-HCl pH 7.9, 0.1 mM DTT, 0.1 mM EDTA, 0.5% Glycerol] was applied. A final wash of the coexemplarylumn is done with column cleaning buffer.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"F4D36C56A24D4DFD86D2A5208FEE4AA3","order_id":2,"type_id":17,"title":"result","source":{"body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/sd7fhn6.png\" \/><\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"5C894FB29D7F4F4096131840E122A955","order_id":3,"type_id":26,"title":"notes","source":{"id":0,"parent_id":0,"uri":"","title":"","body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">An exemplary image of the MonoQ chromatogram is shown in the 'expected results' section. The star marked line indicates the peak of the RNA polymerase. Fractions around this peak are loaded onto an SDS gel.<\/div><\/div>","created_on":0,"changed_on":0,"creator":{"name":" ","affiliation":"","affiliations":[],"username":"","link":null,"image":{"source":"","placeholder":""},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false},"comments":[]}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#FFED92","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":871724,"guid":"86991DEC2C1544078A2937A24DBA7D27","previous_id":871723,"previous_guid":"955BBE57652E4070BCB038EBE5FF74AF","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"10E6023C4A0F4A81A71F42DAE2300D25","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"RNA polymerase sample preparation"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F3E9208C7CE34B1AB54A019B5085F96A","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Again fractions containing RNA polymerase were concentrated with Vivaspin\u00ae 500 \u00b5L 5K ultrafiltration spin columns washed with loading buffer several times. Use the same ultrafiltration spin column to change buffer and concentrate RNA polymerase with storage buffer. To validate your sample one can use western blotting or mass spectrometry. Samples are stored at -20\u00b0C.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"D14D7DD0258643C4AA0F3421E1A3DBE3","order_id":2,"type_id":17,"title":"result","source":{"body":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/pr-journal\/sebfhn6.png\" \/><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Typical result after Ion-exchange chromatography<\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#EA9F6C","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[{"id":119782,"mol_weight":0,"name":"HiTrap Heparin HP affinity column","linfor":"","url":"","sku":"17040701","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Ge Life Sciences","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.gelifesciences.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":16},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":119783,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Mono Q\u00ae 5\/50 GL","linfor":"","url":"","sku":"GE17-5166-01","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Ge Life Sciences","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.gelifesciences.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":16},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol can be used to purifiy DNA-dependent RNA polymerase from <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Synechococcus elongatus <\/span><span>PCC<\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"> 7942 <\/span><span>by heparin and ion-exchange chromatography.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1579683624}